krrood.ormatic.eql_interface#

Exceptions#

EQLTranslationError

Raised when an EQL expression cannot be translated into SQLAlchemy.

UnsupportedQueryTypeError

Raised when an unsupported query type is encountered.

UnsupportedOperatorError

Raised when an unsupported operator is encountered.

UnsupportedQuantifierError

Raised when an unsupported quantifier is encountered.

AttributeResolutionError

Raised when an attribute cannot be resolved.

MissingDAOError

Raised when a DAO class cannot be found for a type.

DomainExtractionError

Raised when a value cannot be extracted from a domain.

Classes#

VariableTypeExtractor

Extracts underlying Variable and its python type from a leaf-like node.

AttributeChainResolver

Resolves attribute chains for EQL Attribute expressions.

RelationshipResolver

Resolves relationships and foreign keys for DAO classes.

OperatorMapper

Maps EQL operators to SQLAlchemy expressions.

DomainValueExtractor

Extracts values from EQL Variable/Literal domains.

JoinManager

Manages JOIN operations for the EQL translator.

EQLTranslator

Translate an EQL query into an SQLAlchemy query.

class krrood.ormatic.eql_interface.JoinManager#

Manages JOIN operations for the EQL translator.

Tracks both which relationship paths have been joined and the SQLAlchemy alias used for each path so that downstream column references can bind to the correct FROM element without triggering implicit joins.

aliases_by_path: dict[tuple[type, str], typing_extensions.Any]#
joined_tables: set[type]#
add_path_join(dao_class: type, attribute_name: str, alias: typing_extensions.Any) → None#

Register a path-based JOIN and its alias.

Parameters:

  • dao_class – The DAO class

  • attribute_name – The attribute name

  • alias – The SQLAlchemy aliased entity used for the join

is_path_joined(dao_class: type, attribute_name: str) → bool#

Check if a path has already been joined.

Parameters:

  • dao_class – The DAO class

  • attribute_name – The attribute name

Returns:

True if already joined

class krrood.ormatic.eql_interface.EQLTranslator#

Translate an EQL query into an SQLAlchemy query.

This assumes the query has a structure like: - quantifier (an/the)

  • select like (entity, setof)
    • Root Condition

      • child 1

      • child 2

      • …

eql_query: krrood.entity_query_language.symbolic.SymbolicExpression#
session: sqlalchemy.orm.Session#
sql_query: typing_extensions.Optional[sqlalchemy.Select] = None#
join_manager: JoinManager#
property quantifier: krrood.entity_query_language.symbolic.SymbolicExpression#

Get the quantifier from the query.

property select_like: typing_extensions.Any#

Get the select-like expression from the query.

property root_condition: krrood.entity_query_language.symbolic.SymbolicExpression#

Get the root condition from the query.
